      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A POUND OF SALT (4) on the quick back-up and has his hoof on the till. Drifted back early from the inside gate and motored late with a respectable fourth over 1512m at Port Macquarie. Tempo suits and expected to go close. INDIFFERENCE (1) has a good record over this course and distance and on the quick turnaround with the 4kg claimer aboard. Chipped away late for a tidy third over 1512m at Port Macquarie. Finds a more suitable contest and can get the job done. RING AHOY (5) consistent gelding kept fresh for this. Rounded up inferior opposition with a comfortable win over 2245m at Grafton. Gets in light with the in-form apprentice aboard. Each-way. BELLINI SPRITZ (6) is a capable mare who freshened up well with a solid second over 2100m at this track. Maps well and should handle the drop in distance.",
